#1. unmodified -> modified = git restore filename
                  (edit)
	
#2. unmodified -> modified -> staged = git restore --staged filename
                   (edit)              (or)
	                                     git rm --cached filename

#3. untracked -> staged = git restore --staged filename

git repository directory structure:
-----------------------------------
The .git directory holds the information about the repository and objects that are commited into the repository. when we issue git init inside the empty directory, the git creates the .git directory initializing the empty repository with the below directory structure inside it.

.git (directory)
|-hooks
|-info
|-objects
|-logs
|-refs
--------
|-config
|-index
|-HEAD






